      "message": "Is TSYNC exposed via the prctl? I think this has to go through the new seccomp() system call. This is how we engage Seccomp-TSYNC in Chromium:\n\nhttps://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/sandbox/linux/seccomp-bpf/sandbox_bpf.cc?q\u003dsandbox_bpf\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026dr\u003dC\u0026l\u003d265\n\nI think these flags come from the selftest file (http://lxr.free-electrons.com/source/tools/testing/selftests/seccomp/seccomp_bpf.c?v\u003d4.5#L52), but I don\u0027t see other references to them (e.g., in http://lxr.free-electrons.com/source/include/uapi/linux/prctl.h?v\u003d3.18#L67). I do see references to SECCOMP_FILTER_FLAG_TSYNC though.",
