      "writtenOn": "2016-09-08T20:13:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "TSYNC availability should be testable with a NULL filter:\n\nret \u003d seccomp(SECCOMP_SET_MODE_FILTER, SECCOMP_FILTER_FLAG_TSYNC, NULL);\n\nIf this returns ENOSYS, the kernel lacks seccomp syscall support.\n\nIf this returns EINVAL, the kernel supports the seccomp syscall but not TSYNC.\n\nIf this returns EFAULT, the kernel supports TSYNC (and is correctly refusing the bad filter).",
      "parentUuid": "f6241f97_e5d1361f",
